In [2]:
plt.figure (figsize = (8.333, 5.208), dpi = 326)

m = Basemap (projection = 'merc', llcrnrlat = '-80', urcrnrlat = '80',\
             llcrnrlon = '-180', urcrnrlon = '180', lat_ts = '20',\
             resolution = 'h')
m.drawcoastlines (linewidth = 0.5, color = '#E8175D')
m.drawcountries (color = '#CC527A')
m.fillcontinents (color = '#363636', lake_color = '#474747')
m.drawmapboundary (fill_color = '#474747')

loc = ['Belize', 'Japan', 'Venezuela']
lon = [-88.366669, 137.000000, -66.916664]
lat = [16.513889, 36.000000, 10.500000]

x, y = m (lon, lat)

# for lab, xpt, ypt in zip (loc, x, y):
#    plt.text (xpt + 600000, ypt, lab)

m.plot (x, y, 'bo', markersize = 5, color = '#FFFFFF')

plt.savefig ('world_map.png', bbox_inches = 'tight', pad_inches = 0)
plt.show ()

plt.figure (figsize = (8.333, 5.208), dpi = 326)

ht = Basemap (projection = 'merc', llcrnrlat = '17.75', urcrnrlat = '20.25',\
             llcrnrlon = '-74.75', urcrnrlon = '-71.5', lat_ts = '20',\
             resolution = 'h')

ht.drawcoastlines (linewidth = 0.5, color = '#E8175D')
ht.drawcountries (color = '#CC527A')
ht.drawstates (color = '#E8175D')
ht.drawrivers (linewidth = 1, color = '#FFFFFF')
ht.fillcontinents (color = '#363636', lake_color = '#474747')
ht.drawmapboundary (fill_color = '#474747')

plt.savefig ('haiti.png', bbox_inches = 'tight', pad_inches = 0)
plt.show ()
